parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Premature transmission failure can cause the vehicle to shudder, jerk, or vibrate violently, leading to loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: especially at low speeds; transmission slipping or surging; difficulty accelerating; vehicle stalls or hesitates to move; warning lights may not illuminate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the clutch master cylinder can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
clutch pedal sticks to the floor
clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the intake air temperature sensor can cause the vehicle to run poorly, leading to decreased performance and potentially causing accidents.
The failure of the liftgate latch can cause the liftgate to open unexpectedly, leading to a safety issue where anyone or anything can fall out of the vehicle.
symptoms: The liftgate latch fails to secure
the liftgate door open indicator comes on
no alarm sounds prior to the failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The spontaneous shattering of the sunroof can cause a loud noise, startling the driver, and potentially leading to loss of control of the vehicle or accidents.
symptoms: making a loud noise similar to a gunshot
glass falls down inside the vehicle
no warning lights or symptoms prior to the failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The stalling and shutting off of the vehicle can cause accidents, especially if it occurs while driving on the highway, and can leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: especially when the temperature is hot outside or when sitting in idle for a while in traffic.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The vehicle rolling backwards can cause accidents, especially if it occurs when people are getting out of the vehicle, and can lead to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle begins to roll backwards down a driveway or slope
even when the parking brake is engaged
and can cause damage to the vehicle or other objects.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can lead to the deployment of airbags without warning, or the failure to deploy airbags in the event of an accident, which can result in serious injury or death.
symptoms: The airbag warning light on the passenger's side continuously flashes
the front and rear passenger's side seat airbag deploys inadvertently
the airbag warning indicator remains illuminated
the airbag system fails to recognize a passenger in the seat
the airbag system incorrectly classifies adult passengers as children and turns the airbag off
the seat belt light is on all the time whether the passenger is in the vehicle or not.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag sensor can cause the airbag system to malfunction, leading to the deployment of airbags without warning, or the failure to deploy airbags in the event of an accident, which can result in serious injury or death.
symptoms: The airbag warning light on the passenger's side continuously flashes
the airbag system fails to recognize a passenger in the seat
the airbag system incorrectly classifies adult passengers as children and turns the airbag off.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The inadvertent deployment of airbags can cause serious injury or death, especially if it occurs while the vehicle is in motion.
symptoms: The front and rear passenger's side seat airbag deploys inadvertently
